persona_tip: Nous utilisons le service Persona de Mozilla pour identifier les utilisateurs se connectant à l'application. Pourquoi ? 1/ nous leur faisons plus confiance qu'à nous même pour conserver votre mot-de-passe en sécurité. 2/ comme d'autres services utilisent Persona, cela vous fait moins de mot-de-passe à retenir ! 3/ Mozilla ne donne ni ne demande l'accès à aucune de vos données. Vous n'avez pas encore de compte ? Cliquez le bouton 'Sign in with your Email' et suivez les instructions.
pitch-transition: This is an experiment about resources and capabilities. Given a resource you have or you look for, what are your possibilities? Make, give, get, lend, borrow, rent, buy, sell, upcycle, recycle... This is about mapping possibilities and alternatives to straight consumerism.
pitch-just-books: That's already a wide program isn't it? Let's start small: just mapping books in your network or nearby, available for giving, lending or selling. Peer to peer first, but integrating local libraries and booksellers in the map as soon as possible.
pitch-open-knowledge: Information on resources should be free and open for citizens to be empowered in their daily choices. What if our daily interactions with resources, our transactions, were contributing to make everyone's knowledge on those resources grow? **Inventaire is an experiment to make a step in this direction**, starting by using **[Wikidata](http://wikidata.org/)** - the awesome public database gathering facts for Wikipedia - as a starting point to gather data on resources.
pitch-open-source: Closed centralized systems grow dependancy, while contributive, free and open knowledge needs trust to thrive. **[Inventaire's code](http://github.com/maxlath/inventaire/) is a Free/Open software published under the [AGPL3 licence](http://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html)**. Today, the Inventaire experiment has a centralized technical architecture as decentralized architectures are hard to achieve: efforts are focused on bringing users value from open knowledge with as little pain as possible, but finding ways to overcome this centralization is part of the trip. This expirement isnt the ultimate tool to manage information on resources, just an attempt to make further steps toward better tools.
pitch-your-data: You can already download your inventory data at any time. In the future, data should be interoperable and synchronizable with Personal Data Store.
contributions_welcome:
Feedbacks and contributions are very welcome!
